  fat: 34.8 g
  saturated fat: 13.5 g
  carbohydrates: 86.3 g
  sugar: 36.5 g
  protein: 20.5 g
  sodium: 3.3 g
  serving size: 748
cuisine: European
author: Sam Richards
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/cheesy-mediterranean-style-chickpea-pie-66e066eba3dfaa8a349aa6cb
time required: 45 minutes
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @puff pastry sheet{1/2%pack} from your fridge to allow it to come to room temperature.

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and seeded) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2-3cm chunks. Trim the @aubergine{1}(trimmed and cut into roughly 2cm pieces), then cut into roughly 2cm pieces.

Pop the pepper and aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the #oven{} is hot, roast the veg on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{3}(trimmed and halved lengthways). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large baking tray. Sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the chickpeas, @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the aubergine and pepper have cooked, stir them into the sauce in the frying pan. Stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Roast the carrots on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Transfer your vegetable filling to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Cover the dish with the puff pastry, pressing it over the side of the dish or just sitting it on top, then trimming off any excess.

Make a small hole in the middle to allow steam to escape.

> TIP: Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Bake your pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once it's out of the oven, allow it to stand for ~{2%minutes}.

When the carrots have 5 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven. Drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp} and toss to coat. Return to the oven for the remaining time.

Once the carrots are roasted, share the cheesy veg pie between your plates. Serve with the roasted carrots on the side.

Enjoy!